            <div class="text-md flex items-center gap-4 font-bold">
              <AstroLogo height="40" width="40" /> Astro Base
            </div>
            <div class="text-md flex items-center gap-4 font-bold">
              <Pocketbase height="40" width="40" /> PocketBase Backend
            </div>
            <div class="text-md flex items-center gap-4 font-bold">
              <img src="/public/tanstack.png" height="40" width="40" /> TanStack
              CSR
            </div>
            <div class="text-md flex items-center gap-4 font-bold">
              <SSTLogo height="40" width="40" /> SST Deployments
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- <div class="divider"></div> -->
        </div>

        <!-- <CallToAciton client:only="react" /> -->
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
      <div class="prose ml-28 my-32 prose-lg max-w-lg">
        <p class="text-3xl">
          You are being <span class="font-black">lied to.</span>
          <br /> And the <span id="liars" class="font-black"
            >liars are profiting</span
          > off of it.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6">Web development doesn't need to be hard.</p>
        <p class="mt-6">
          With modern tooling and the right guidance building for the web is
          actually very simple. But there is money to be found in making you
          scared and conditioning you into learned helplessness.
        </p>
        <p>
          Large companies are investing heavily in making tech stacks obtuse,
          intimidating, and dependant on their infrastructure they assure you is
          too complex for you to even begin to understand.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col mx-12">
        <div class="mockup-code mt-20">
          <pre
            data-prefix="$"
            class="text-secondary"><code>npm create astro@latest -- --template <span class="text-success">technomancy-dev/spellbook</span></code></pre>
          <pre
            data-prefix=">"
            class="text-warning"><code>installing...</code></pre>
          <pre
            data-prefix=">"
            class="text-success"><code>Time to Ship!</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="prose mt-12">
          <p class="text-3xl font-black">It's not just the companies</p>
          <p>
            Not only are their pockets deep enough to pay off every mustached
            influencer they can find, but their tentacles run wide.
          </p>
          <p>
            Many indiehackers have bought into <span
              id="complexity"
              class="text-xl font-black"
            >
              The ComplexityStack<span class="text-base font-normal align-super"
                >â„¢</span
              >
            </span>
            and have profited off of promising to help you make sense of it.
          </p>
          <p>They prey on your insecurity and sell you hope.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div data-theme="lofi" class="flex py-28 px-28">

